{{italic title}}
A '''''de excommunicato deliberando''''' is a writ which issued out of chancery to release a prisoner from the county jail after the bishop had certified the prisoner's reconciliation with the Church, following his arrest and imprisonment under a writ [[Writ De Excommunicato Capiendo Act 1562|de excommunicato capiendo]].<ref>[http://legaldictionary.lawin.org/de-excommunicato-deliberando/ "De Excommunicato Deliberando" Legal Dictionaries of the Encyclopedia of Law Project]</ref><ref>[http://definitions.uslegal.com/d/de-excommunicato-deliberando/ "De Excommunicato Deliberando" Law & Legal Definition, U.S. Legal]</ref><ref>[http://thelawdictionary.org/de-excommunicato-deliberando/ "De Excommunicato Deliberando" The Law Dictionary, Featuring Black's Law Dictionary Free Online Legal Dictionary 2nd Ed.]</ref>

